---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy for [C3_NAME] apps. All data is stored locally on your device. No servers, no tracking, no accounts."
>

<section style="padding:3rem 1.5rem 1rem;">
  <div class="content">
    <p class="section-label">Legal</p>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section legal-page" style="padding-top:1rem;">
  <div class="content">
    <p class="effective-date">Effective date: February 26, 2026</p>

    <p>
      [C3_NAME] (&ldquo;we,&rdquo; &ldquo;us,&rdquo; or &ldquo;our&rdquo;) is a
      501(c)(3) nonprofit organization. This Privacy Policy describes how our
      apps handle information. The short version: <strong>our apps do not collect,
      transmit, or store your personal data on any server we operate.</strong>
      All data stays on your device.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Data We Collect</h2>
    <p>
      Our apps do not collect personal information. Specifically:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>We do not create or require user accounts.</li>
      <li>We do not collect email addresses, phone numbers, or any contact information.</li>
      <li>We do not use advertising networks or analytics platforms.</li>
      <li>We do not track app usage, session lengths, or feature interactions.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. Data Stored On Your Device</h2>
    <p>
      Our apps store data locally on your device. This data never leaves your device
      unless you explicitly share or export it. Examples of locally stored data:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>One Second A Day:</strong> video clips, thumbnails, compilation
        files, clip metadata (dates, tags, GPS coordinates if enabled),
        face recognition embeddings (if enabled), and app preferences.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      This data is stored in your device&rsquo;s private app storage and is not
      accessible to other apps without your explicit action (e.g., using the
      system share sheet).
    </p>

    <h2>3. Optional Features That Access Device Data</h2>
    <p>
      Some features request access to device capabilities. All are opt-in and
      can be disabled in app settings:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Camera:</strong> Used to record video clips. Video is saved
        locally; nothing is transmitted.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Microphone:</strong> Used to capture audio with video clips.
        Audio is saved locally with the clip.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Location (GPS):</strong> Used to tag clips with a location
        name (e.g., &ldquo;New York, NY&rdquo;). Location data is stored
        locally with the clip metadata and is never transmitted to us.
        Reverse geocoding is performed offline using bundled city data.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Photo library:</strong> Used to import existing photos or
        videos into the app. We read only the files you explicitly select.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Notifications:</strong> Used to send daily reminder
        notifications. Notification scheduling is handled entirely on-device.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Face recognition:</strong> Used to automatically tag people
        in clips. Face embeddings are computed on-device using a locally
        bundled model (MobileFaceNet). No face data is transmitted.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. App Update Checks</h2>
    <p>
      Apps installed via direct APK download (not through Google Play) may
      perform a version check at launch. This is a simple HTTP GET request to
      our website:
    </p>
    <pre style="background:var(--color-bg-alt);border:1px solid var(--color-border);border-radius:var(--radius);padding:0.75rem 1rem;font-size:0.875rem;overflow-x:auto;">GET https://[C3_DOMAIN].org/apps/[app-name]/version.json</pre>
    <p>
      This request carries only standard HTTP headers (no personal identifiers).
      It checks whether a newer version is available and, if so, displays an
      in-app banner. No data about you or your device is sent to us.
    </p>
    <p>
      Apps installed via Google Play do not perform this check; Google Play
      handles updates directly.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>
      Our apps do not integrate with any third-party analytics, advertising,
      crash-reporting, or social media services.
    </p>
    <p>
      Apps installed via Google Play are subject to Google Play&rsquo;s own
      privacy practices for the distribution and update process. We do not
      control or receive data from Google Play beyond standard developer
      console metrics (crash counts, install counts &mdash; aggregated,
      not personally identifiable).
    </p>

    <h2>6. Children&rsquo;s Privacy (COPPA)</h2>
    <p>
      Our apps are designed for use by adults and families. They are not
      directed to children under 13. Because our apps do not collect any
      personal information from anyone, we are confident they comply with the
      Children&rsquo;s Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA).
    </p>
    <p>
      If you believe a child under 13 has provided us with personal information,
      please contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@[C3_DOMAIN].org">privacy@[C3_DOMAIN].org</a>
      and we will address the concern promptly.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Security</h2>
    <p>
      Because we do not operate servers that store your data, there is no
      central database to breach. Your data is protected by your device&rsquo;s
      own security mechanisms (screen lock, encryption, etc.).
    </p>
    <p>
      Our app code is open source and publicly auditable. If you discover a
      security vulnerability, please report it to
      <a href="mailto:security@[C3_DOMAIN].org">security@[C3_DOMAIN].org</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy as our apps evolve. If we make
      material changes, we will update the effective date above and, where
      appropriate, provide notice within the app. Continued use of our apps
      after an update constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about this policy or our data practices:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@[C3_DOMAIN].org">privacy@[C3_DOMAIN].org</a></li>
      <li>Mail: [C3_NAME], [Registered address — add before launch]</li>
    </ul>

  </div>
</section>

</Layout>
